14:57.923 --> 14:59.695
More for me.

14:59.720 --> 15:01.512
This night couldn't get any better.

15:01.537 --> 15:03.526
Who's ready for ice cream?

15:03.551 --> 15:05.283
Ooh, I stand corrected.

15:07.047 --> 15:09.337
Don't be vanilla bean.
Don't be vanilla bean.

15:09.362 --> 15:11.285
- Is it vanilla bean? Oh.
- Mm-hmm.

15:13.327 --> 15:15.590
So you're saying I can't get
any of this vanilla bean

15:15.615 --> 15:17.468
because of that vanilla bean?

15:19.353 --> 15:21.113
Just stay strong, my brother.

15:21.138 --> 15:22.204
What's going on?

15:22.229 --> 15:23.286
Oh, White Gandhi,

15:23.311 --> 15:24.556
Nerd Gandhi and Broke Gandhi

15:24.581 --> 15:26.434
are on a hunger strike.

15:28.152 --> 15:29.128
A hunger strike?

15:29.153 --> 15:30.447
- Mm-hmm.
- Yes.

15:30.472 --> 15:32.472
We are tired of Pop's dictatorship.

15:32.541 --> 15:33.886
We demand democracy.

15:33.911 --> 15:34.910
And cobbler.

15:36.638 --> 15:39.547
Hot, bubbly cobbler
with-with-with-with cold,

15:39.572 --> 15:42.591
creamy ice cream, where-where
the cobbler starts

15:42.616 --> 15:44.543
to melt the ice cream ever so slightly.

15:44.568 --> 15:46.454
And-and real specks of vanilla beans

15:46.479 --> 15:50.111
start cascading down the
side of a peach, while my...

15:50.136 --> 15:52.424
Damn, man, just have a piece.

15:53.009 --> 15:54.953
Okay, and here you go.

15:54.978 --> 15:56.196
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, wait.

15:56.221 --> 15:57.596
No, he doesn't get cobbler.

15:57.621 --> 15:59.666
He didn't even try his catfish.

15:59.691 --> 16:00.776
Ah, come on, baby.

16:00.801 --> 16:02.536
Give the boy some cobbler.
It's probably the first time

16:02.561 --> 16:04.227
he ever tried food with flavor.

16:07.066 --> 16:08.813
I don't care.

16:08.838 --> 16:10.520
The rules are the rules.

16:10.730 --> 16:12.169
And listen, little man,

16:12.194 --> 16:13.634
you may not understand this right now,

16:13.659 --> 16:15.112
but I'm trying to help you.

16:15.219 --> 16:17.459
This feels like the opposite.

16:19.312 --> 16:22.177
Look, Grover, you can't go through life

16:22.202 --> 16:23.962
with your mind already made up

16:23.987 --> 16:26.619
about things that you
like or don't like.

16:26.710 --> 16:27.862
You're going to miss out

16:27.887 --> 16:30.268
- on a lot of stuff.
- Like what?

16:30.821 --> 16:32.213
Well, look at Marty.

16:32.335 --> 16:35.297
He didn't like working on
cars when he was a kid,

16:35.322 --> 16:38.195
but I made him, and
that's where he started

16:38.220 --> 16:40.613
to enjoy working on machines.

16:40.664 --> 16:43.057
And that turned him into
a successful engineer.

16:43.511 --> 16:45.088
Wait a minute, Dad, are you
seriously taking credit

16:45.113 --> 16:47.051
for me becoming an engineer?

16:48.715 --> 16:51.015
And-and Malcolm hated books,

16:51.170 --> 16:52.473
but I made him read to me

16:52.498 --> 16:54.175
every day when I took him to school.

16:54.289 --> 16:55.752
We only lived a mile away,

16:55.777 --> 16:58.820
so it took us five
years to finish <i> Roots.</i>

17:00.166 --> 17:02.686
But then you started reading Malcolm X

17:02.711 --> 17:04.579
and Maya Angelou, and James Baldwin,

17:04.605 --> 17:07.369
and look at you, following
in their footsteps.

17:07.395 --> 17:08.694
Yeah? How?

17:08.719 --> 17:10.686
Organizing sit-ins.

17:11.146 --> 17:14.833
I mean, granted, it's for
little white kids, but still.

17:15.838 --> 17:17.798
Calvin, please, you're one to talk.

17:17.823 --> 17:19.486
You hate trying new things.

17:19.511 --> 17:20.577
That's not true.

17:20.602 --> 17:21.888
You just flipped out the other day

17:21.914 --> 17:24.208
when I put raspberry
vinaigrette on your salad.

17:24.233 --> 17:27.730
That's because dressings are
supposed to be creamy, Tina.

17:28.540 --> 17:30.978
Ranch, Thousand Island, blue cheese.

17:31.003 --> 17:33.757
If my carrot can't stand
up in it, I don't want it.

17:35.721 --> 17:39.181
Look, my point is,

17:39.361 --> 17:40.963
you don't know what you like

17:40.988 --> 17:43.685
until you at least give it a try.

17:44.302 --> 17:46.459
Okay. I'll try it.

17:46.484 --> 17:47.568
Oh.

17:47.593 --> 17:48.905
Okay.

17:49.309 --> 17:50.575
What do you think?

17:50.600 --> 17:53.688
Mmm. It's good.

17:54.073 --> 17:55.852
It tastes like chicken fingers.

17:57.638 --> 18:00.545
Now you can have some cobbler.

18:00.720 --> 18:03.099
Hey, way to stay strong, little man.

18:03.124 --> 18:05.327
You know, you are the
only kid to ever get more

18:05.352 --> 18:08.155
of an explanation than
"Because I said so."

18:09.454 --> 18:12.284
This is cause for celebration.

18:12.719 --> 18:14.152
Oh.

18:15.052 --> 18:16.724
What you think you're doing?

18:16.749 --> 18:18.133
Why can't I have some?

18:18.158 --> 18:20.479
Because I said so.

18:22.832 --> 18:25.766
I can't believe what a
disaster tonight is.

18:25.791 --> 18:28.888
Instead of taking your
mind off of things,

18:28.913 --> 18:30.579
I just made everything worse.

18:31.143 --> 18:32.976
No, you didn't.

18:33.554 --> 18:35.388
You did everything right.

18:35.642 --> 18:38.610
I don't know why I couldn't
just relax and enjoy it.

18:38.635 --> 18:40.334
Well, you got a lot going on.

18:40.359 --> 18:42.659
Yeah, but I always have a lot going on.

18:43.366 --> 18:45.398
I think this is something more.

18:45.466 --> 18:46.832
What do you mean?

18:48.380 --> 18:50.638
Was it wrong of me to
make us move here?

18:50.715 --> 18:51.914
What?

18:52.084 --> 18:53.353
I'm the one who got the job

18:53.378 --> 18:55.132
and made us move to California.

18:55.157 --> 18:56.533
I made us leave all of our family,

18:56.558 --> 18:58.631
our friends, Grover's school.

18:58.685 --> 19:00.752
I uprooted everything.

19:00.960 --> 19:03.590
Gemma, you didn't make us do anything.

19:03.615 --> 19:05.315
We decided together.

19:05.420 --> 19:06.880
Are you sure?

19:06.905 --> 19:11.499
Well, maybe it was 60-40, but...

19:11.945 --> 19:15.018
I was an enthusiastic 40.

19:15.594 --> 19:18.589
Dave, you're an
enthusiastic everything.

19:20.401 --> 19:22.085
We're a team, Gemma.

19:22.459 --> 19:24.290
Like Maverick and Goose?

19:25.923 --> 19:28.334
I've never loved you more.

19:28.558 --> 19:30.804
Ugh, I guess that makes me Goose.

19:30.829 --> 19:33.681
Well, yeah, look at me.
You're definitely Goose.

19:35.982 --> 19:38.101
Gemma, I'd follow you anywhere.

19:38.566 --> 19:41.167
All I ever want to be is close to you.

19:41.568 --> 19:43.214
I know, sweetie.

19:43.239 --> 19:44.481
I love you.

19:44.904 --> 19:46.678
And I love you.

19:49.051 --> 19:53.265
You know, even though this isn't
exactly what you had in mind,

19:53.798 --> 19:57.003
we are pretty close right now.

19:57.356 --> 19:59.159
We are, aren't we?

19:59.184 --> 20:00.701
What do you think?

20:01.386 --> 20:03.538
Goose, you big stud,

20:03.563 --> 20:06.700
take me to bed or lose me forever.

